// BT-2207: E2E fixture for `SystemNavigation unusedSelectors`.
//
// `UnusedDemo` has two helper methods:
// - `usedHelper` IS sent (by `caller`), so it must NOT be flagged as unused.
// - `neverCalledHelper` is sent nowhere in the workspace, so it MUST be flagged
//   as a dead-method candidate.

Object subclass: UnusedDemo

  // Sends `usedHelper` — this is the source-visible use that keeps `usedHelper`
  // out of the unused report.
  caller => self usedHelper

  // Sent by `caller` above, so it is used.
  usedHelper => 42

  // Sent by nobody anywhere — the genuine dead-method candidate.
  neverCalledHelper => 99
